tasks.description:
Bundle of frontend performance fixes: fix the broken chunk retry logic, lazy-load 10 more conditional modals, fix the unbounded dependsOn cache, and improve the GraphQL cost limit rule.

**1. Fix lazyWithRetry** (`apps/web/src/App.tsx`, lines 16-30):
The current implementation has a bug — the retry path recursively calls `lazyWithRetry()` which returns a `LazyExoticComponent`, not a module promise. The `as never` cast hides this. Replace with an async loop:
```typescript
function lazyWithRetry<T extends ComponentType<unknown>>(
  importFn: () => Promise<{ default: T }>,
  retries = 2,
): React.LazyExoticComponent<T> {
  return lazy(async () => {
    for (let i = 0; i <= retries; i++) {
      try {
        return await importFn();
      } catch (err) {
        if (i === retries) throw err;
        await new Promise((r) => setTimeout(r, 1000));
      }
    }
    throw new Error('Unreachable');
  });
}
```

Move `lazyWithRetry` to a utility file `apps/web/src/utils/lazyWithRetry.ts` so it can be imported by both App.tsx and ProjectDetail.tsx. Export it as a named export.

**2. Lazy-load remaining conditional modals** (`apps/web/src/pages/ProjectDetail.tsx`, lines 27-40):
These 10 modals are eagerly imported but only rendered conditionally behind state flags. Convert them to `lazyWithRetry`:
- `GitHubRepoModal` (line 31, shown when `showGitHubModal`)
- `StandupReportPanel` (line 32, shown when `showStandup`)
- `ProjectHealthPanel` (line 33, shown when `showHealth`)
- `TrendAnalysisPanel` (line 34, shown when `showTrends`)
- `MeetingNotesDialog` (line 35, shown when `showMeetingNotes`)
- `CSVImportModal` (line 36, shown when `showCSVImport`)
- `KnowledgeBaseModal` (line 37, shown when `showKnowledgeBase`)
- `BugReportModal` (line 38, shown when `showBugReport`)
- `PRDBreakdownModal` (line 39, shown when `showPRDBreakdown`)
- `SprintTransitionModal` (line 40, shown when `showTransition`)

Wrap each lazy modal's render site with `<Suspense fallback={<div className="flex items-center justify-center p-8"><div className="animate-spin rounded-full h-8 w-8 border-b-2 border-brand-green" /></div>}>`. Since these are modals that appear on user action, the brief spinner is fine.

**3. Fix dependsOnCache memory leak** (`apps/web/src/utils/taskHelpers.ts`, lines 3-17):
The `dependsOnCache` Map has no size limit. Add a max size of 1000 entries with oldest-entry eviction:
```typescript
const MAX_CACHE_SIZE = 1000;
// ... in parseDependsOn, before .set():
if (dependsOnCache.size >= MAX_CACHE_SIZE) {
  const firstKey = dependsOnCache.keys().next().value;
  if (firstKey !== undefined) dependsOnCache.delete(firstKey);
}
```

**4. Cost limit unknown list field handling** (`apps/api/src/graphql/schema.ts`, around line 155-165):
In the `computeSelectionCost` function, fields NOT in `COST_MAP` that have selection sets (sub-selections) don't get a list multiplier — they recurse with `multiplier = 1`. Fix: if a field has `node.selectionSet` and the field name is NOT in `COST_MAP`, apply `DEFAULT_LIST_MULTIPLIER` (10) as the multiplier. This catches new list fields like `customFieldValues`, `taskAssignees`, etc. that were added after the cost map was written.
